RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 2 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 85. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 40000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FLORIDA-BRED, OR MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ARAK set the pace in the two path, was cued right handed when challenged by an outer rival turning into the stretch, briefly lost the lead while dueling with that foe passing the eighth pole, but dug in and fought on gamely to get back up in the final strides. ONE FAST DREAM raced prominently while up close under a hold from the three path, bid under a drive turning into the lane, stayed on and stuck a head in front of the inner pacesetter while dueling passing the eighth pole, but was repelled to place. CACCIATORE tracked in the four path and was coaxed along into the far turn, tipped out to the five path turning into the stretch and finished evenly for show. RIGHT KARMA raced off the pace in the three path, was cued from the four path into the far turn, urged while swinging out to the six path into the lane, but was one paced. SUNSHINE FROLIC rated in the five path, floated out around the turn and was in the eight path entering the stretch, angled inwards and made no impact. LYTE CRUDE stalked in the two path but faded along the inside turning into the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD OR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUNTLESS DREAMS pressed the pace in the three path, drew clear nearing the quarter pole and widened under a drive in the lane. INDIA PILAGA (ARG) stalked the pace from the rail, was in a bit tight near the quarter pole, had a clear path at the rail throughout the stretch run and was clearly second best. VACATION SUITE raced off the early pace, advanced four wide around the turn, was forced out turning for home, could not gain on the winner in the lane and was geared down late. HOLLYWOOD HONEY saved ground and failed to menace. DELTA RED set the pace in the two path, drifted out leaving the quarter pole, was clipped behind and retreated. SHE KNOWS IT ALL was off slow and outrun while racing five wide. LAW MACHINE raced in range three wide between foes, clipped heels nearing the three-sixteenths pole, fell, quickly regained her feet and walked off. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT NEARING THE THREE-SIXTEENTHS POLE AND DISQUALIFIED DELTA RED FROM FIFTH TO LAST FOR INTERFERENCE.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 22000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD OR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANOTHERDAYGONEBY set the pace in the two path, drew clear from the pace rivals near the quarter pole, was headed by a rail-rallying MISS UCRANIA in midstretch, was lightly bumped by that foe near the sixteenth pole, dueled outside to the wire and narrowly prevailed. MISS UCRANIA saved ground off the pace, closed at the rail in upper stretch, took the lead nearing the eighth pole, drifted out and lightly bumped the winner near the sixteenth pole, dueled inside of that foe to the wire and just missed. FIND YOUR PASSION dueled three wide down the backstretch, chased in the three path around the turn, could not keep pace with the top two in upper stretch but stayed on for the show. BLACK ICE raced in range four wide and weakened in the lane. TROTTING GEAR dueled between foes while the rider frequently reached forward in an apparent attempt to adjust equipment then faded after a half. YLANG YLANG failed to menace while racing four wide. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT NEAR THE SIXTEENTH POLE AND FOUND NO REASON TO ALTER THE ORIGINAL ORDER OF FINISH.
